<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1543,2010]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1663,1689]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tube shining white, smooth, without ornamentation (
<figureCitation box="[985,1071,1664,1690]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="19.[151,255,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[262,1324,196,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-112@19.[260,1327,194,1794]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 5. A: Ficopomatus enigmaticus, from California, LACM-AHF N1873. A, operculum, lateral view. B–D: Ficopomatus miamiensis, from Sinaloa, UMAR-Poly 51. B, operculum, lateral view. C, collar chaeta. From Panama, USNM 58659. D, operculum, lateral view. E–G: Hyalopomatus biformis, from Alaska, LACM-AHF N10714. E, thorax, dorsal view. F, operculum, lateral view. G, collar chaeta. H: Hyalopomatus biformis, from California, LACM-AHF Poly 180, holotype of Vermiliopsis biformis, H, operculum, lateral view. I–J: Hyalopomatus mironovi, from central North Pacific. I, tube. J, thorax, branchial crown and operculum, lateral view. (I–J redrawn from Kupriyanova, 1993)." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5I</figureCitation>
). Opercular peduncle smooth. Operculum pear-shaped with distal convex plate (
<figureCitation box="[750,837,1704,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="19.[151,255,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[262,1324,196,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-112@19.[260,1327,194,1794]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 5. A: Ficopomatus enigmaticus, from California, LACM-AHF N1873. A, operculum, lateral view. B–D: Ficopomatus miamiensis, from Sinaloa, UMAR-Poly 51. B, operculum, lateral view. C, collar chaeta. From Panama, USNM 58659. D, operculum, lateral view. E–G: Hyalopomatus biformis, from Alaska, LACM-AHF N10714. E, thorax, dorsal view. F, operculum, lateral view. G, collar chaeta. H: Hyalopomatus biformis, from California, LACM-AHF Poly 180, holotype of Vermiliopsis biformis, H, operculum, lateral view. I–J: Hyalopomatus mironovi, from central North Pacific. I, tube. J, thorax, branchial crown and operculum, lateral view. (I–J redrawn from Kupriyanova, 1993)." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5J</figureCitation>
). Six thoracic chaetigers. Collar with chaetae finand-blade, with basal denticulate expansion and smooth limb and distinct gap between distal limb and basal expansion. “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedict" authorityYear="1887" box="[294,420,1784,1810]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Apomatus</taxonomicName>
” chaetae absent. Thoracic uncini with multiple rows of teeth and gouged peg.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1543,2010]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,301,1823,1849]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Habitat.</emphasis>
Depth: 
<quantity box="[396,495,1824,1850]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="m" value="4.1">4,100 m</quantity>
. Bathyal. On stalks of glass sponges of the genus 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Beaulieu" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[1077,1212,1824,1849]" class="Hexactinellida" family="Hyalonematidae" genus="Hyalonema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphidiscosida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1077,1212,1824,1849]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Hyalonema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, co-occurring with 
<taxonomicName authority="Bastida-Zavala, 2008" authorityName="Bastida-Zavala" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,483,1864,1889]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Bathyvermilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kupriyanovae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[151,483,1864,1889]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bathyvermilia kupriyanovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[491,553,1864,1890]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<emphasis box="[571,592,1864,1889]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">cf</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Beaulieu, S. E." box="[606,796,1864,1890]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="803 - 817" refId="ref33388" refString="Beaulieu, S. E. (2001 b) Life on glass houses: sponge-stalk communities in the deep sea. Marine Biology, 138, 803 - 817." type="journal article" year="2001">Beaulieu 2001b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
